For the database image:
	Build the database with:
		docker build -t kilo/iss_2021-db_i .

	Strip the image with:
		./strip-db.sh
	
	Run the stripped image with:
		docker run --net kilo/iss_2021_n --ip 203.0.113.88 --hostname db.cyber.test -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD="CorrectHorseBatteryStaple" -e MYSQL_DATABASE="iss_db" --name kilo_iss_2021-db_c kilo/iss_2021-db_i-stripped

	Prepare the db with:
		docker exec -i kilo_iss_2021-db_c mysql -uroot -pCorrectHorseBatteryStaple < sqlconfig/iss_db.sql

	Unfortunatly, the stripping command doesn't work. The log of the error can be founf in dbserver/stripped_log.txt. This is an error that I am unable to find a fix for


For the webserver image:
	Build the image with:
		docker build -t kilo/iss_2021-web_i .
	
	Strip the image with:
		./strip-web.sh

	Run the stripped image with  
		docker run --net kilo/iss_2021_n --ip 203.0.113.77 --hostname www.cyber.test --add-host db.cyber.test:203.0.113.88 -p 80:80 --name kilo_iss_2021-web_c kilo/iss_2021-web_i-stripped

	Unfortunatly, the stripping doesn't work as intended and I am a left with an error that you can find in webserver/stripped_log.txt that I am unable to find a solution for
